<p>Our growing season is intense and relatively short. Heavy spring rains can cause explosive growth, requiring consistent weekly cuts to prevent stress. Conversely, the hot, dry spells we often experience in July and August may require adjusting the mowing height to protect grass roots and conserve water.</p>

